# Kerala Gold Rate Tracker

This repository provides a small Python script that downloads Kerala gold rates from [Keralagold.com](https://www.keralagold.com/), stores the history in CSV and Excel formats, and draws a simple SVG timeline graph.

The script uses only the Python standard library, so it can run in restricted environments where installing packages is not possible.

## Usage

1. Run the tracker (uses live website):

```bash
python goldrate_tracker.py
```

2. If you want to test without internet access, point to the sample HTML file:

```bash
python goldrate_tracker.py --html-file sample_data/sample_kerala_page.html --date 2024-01-01
```

Outputs:

- `gold_rates.csv`: history you can open in Excel or other tools.
- `gold_rates.xlsx`: an Excel workbook generated from the CSV data.
- `gold_rates.svg`: a lightweight line graph of the recorded prices.

You can change the output names/locations using `--csv`, `--excel`, and `--graph` flags.

## How it works

- Fetches the Kerala rate page with a browser-like user agent.
- Looks for the price nearest to the text `1 gram`/`1gm`/`1 g` in the HTML, matching the layout used on Keralagold.com.
- Appends/replaces the entry for the given day in the CSV history.
- Regenerates the Excel workbook and SVG chart from the stored history.

## Notes

- Network access is required to fetch live data. Use `--html-file` for offline testing or debugging.
- Excel support is implemented with raw XML to avoid third-party dependencies; modern spreadsheet apps should read the generated file without issues.
